        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Sorry to necropost here, but I've been affected by this change. I've noticed that neovim has been hard to use on my [DEC VT220](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VT220) and I figured I could turn off ttyfast to fix this - but it didn't work. Found out it was removed from neovim after researching it. Would there be any willingness to consider reintroducing it and making it always on by default?\n",
