        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "If I understand correctly `nottyfast` does two things in vim:\r\n\r\n- disable semantic linewrap. This was reimplemented recently (#8915) and could easily be placed behind an if statement (using the `option_set` mechanism).\r\n- more aggressive use of scrolling, even when the terminal didn't support the exact scrolling region. This could be re-implemented in some cases, using the existing `invalid_regions` logic in `tui.c` . For instance scroll the entire screen to scroll one single window, and then repaint the statusline and cmdline afterwards.",
            "created_at": "2018-10-18T19:34:28Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/1045#issuecomment-431134468",
