        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Neovim should actually behave like nottyfast w.r.t scrolling internally **now**\r\n\r\nare you refering the last stable release or HEAD? What about the semantic line wrapping? Can that feature still introduce noticeable lag in slow connections?\r\n\r\n> not sure what the situation is with tmux/screen\r\n\r\nThe difference in *'lag when moving around'* is indeed more noticeable when using tmux, but that can just be due to the overhead of using a multiplexer.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure on how to benchmark/report this quantitatively, it really boils down to the general *snappiness* feeling.",
